<tales>
    <tale>
        <metadata>
            <title>Sweetheart Roland</title>
            <year>1857</year>
            <author>Jacob and Wilhelm Grimm</author>
            <translator>D.L Ashliman</translator>
            <language>English</language>
            <number>56</number>
        </metadata>
        <story>
            <p>Once upon a time there was a woman who was truly<character marital-status="unmarried"
                    child-status="mother" reference="witch">a witch</character>. <act type="being"
                    agent="witch" receiver="daughters" effect="ambiguous">She had two
                    daughters,</act>
                <character child-status="childless" marital-status="unmarried"
                    reference="witch_daughter">one ugly and wicked,</character> whom <act
                    type="doing" agent="witch" receiver="witch_daughter" effect="benevolent">she
                    loved because she was her own daughter,</act> and <character
                    child-status="childless" marital-status="unmarried" reference="heroine">one
                    beautiful and good,</character> whom <act type="doing" agent="witch"
                    receiver="heroine" effect="hostile">she hated, because she was her
                    stepdaughter.</act>
                <act type="doing" agent="heroine" effect="ambiguous">The <character
                        reference="heroine" marital-status="unmarried" child-status="childless"
                        >stepdaughter</character> had a beautiful apron,</act>
                <act type="being" effect="hostile" agent="witch_daughter" receiver="heroine"
                    io="apron">which the other <character child-status="childless"
                        marital-status="unmarried" reference="witch_daughter">girl</character>
                    wanted so much that she became envious, </act>and <act type="doing"
                    agent="witch_daughter" receiver="witch" effect="hostile" io="apron">she told her
                    mother that she just had to have that apron.</act>
                <dialogue speaker="witch" stateofbeing="negative">"Be still, <character
                        reference="witch_daughter" marital-status="unmarried"
                        child-status="childless">my child,</character>" said the <character
                        child-status="mother" marital-status="unmarried" reference="witch">old
                        woman,</character> "and <act type="doing" agent="witch"
                        receiver="witch_daughter" effect="benevolent" io="apron">you shall have
                        it.</act> Your <act type="being" agent="heroine" effect="hostile"><character
                            reference="heroine" child-status="childless" marital-status="unmarried"
                            >stepsister</character> has long deserved to die,</act> and tonight when
                        <act type="doing" agent="heroine" effect="ambiguous">she is asleep</act>
                    <act type="doing" agent="witch" receiver="heroine" effect="hostile">I will come
                        and chop off her head.</act> Just be sure to lie down at the far side of the
                    bed, and <act type="doing" agent="witch_daughter" receiver="heroine"
                        effect="hostile">push her close to the front."</act></dialogue> It would
                have been all over with <character reference="heroine" marital-status="unmarried"
                    child-status="childless">the poor girl,</character> but just then <act
                    type="doing" agent="heroine" effect="ambiguous">she was standing in a corner,
                    and she overheard everything.</act>
                <act type="doing" agent="witch" receiver="heroine" effect="hostile">She was not
                    allowed to go outside all day long,</act> and at bedtime <act type="doing"
                    agent="witch_daughter" receiver="heroine" effect="hostile">her <character
                        child-status="childless" marital-status="unmarried"
                        reference="witch_daughter">wicked stepsister</character> had her get into
                    bed first,</act> so she would be lying next to the wall. However, after
                    <character reference="witch_daughter" marital-status="unmarried"
                    child-status="childless">the witch's daughter</character> fell asleep, <act
                    type="doing" agent="heroine" receiver="witch_daughter" effect="hostile">the
                        <character child-status="childless" marital-status="unmarried"
                        reference="heroine">stepdaughter</character> gently pushed her to the front
                    side of the bed,</act> and <act type="doing" agent="heroine" effect="benevolent"
                    >she took her place back against the wall.</act> In <act type="doing"
                    agent="witch" effect="hostile">the night <character reference="witch"
                        marital-status="unmarried" child-status="stepmother">the old
                        woman</character> crept into the bedroom holding an ax</act> in her right
                hand while <act type="doing" agent="witch" receiver="heroine" effect="hostile"
                    >feeling with her left hand for anyone lying at the front of the bed. </act>Then
                    <act type="doing" agent="witch" receiver="witch_daughter" effect="hostile">she
                    grasped the axe with both hands and chopped off her own child's head.</act></p>
            <p>After the<character reference="witch" child-status="stepmother"
                    marital-status="unmarried"> witch</character> had gone away, <act type="doing"
                    agent="heroine" receiver="roland" effect="ambiguous"><character
                        child-status="childless" marital-status="unmarried" reference="heroine">the
                        girl</character> got up and went to her sweetheart, whose name was
                    Roland,</act> and knocked at his door. When he came out, <dialogue
                    speaker="heroine" stateofbeing="negative">she said to him, "Listen, dearest
                    Roland, we must flee at once. <act type="doing" agent="witch" receiver="heroine"
                        effect="hostile">My <character reference="witch" marital-status="unmarried"
                            child-status="childless">stepmother</character> tried to kill me,</act>
                    but <act type="doing" agent="witch" receiver="witch_daughter" effect="hostile"
                        >she killed her own child instead.</act> When daylight comes, and she sees
                    what she has done, <act type="being" agent="witch" receiver="heroine_roland"
                        effect="hostile">we'll be lost."</act></dialogue>
                <dialogue speaker="roland" stateofbeing="negative">"You had better take her magic
                    wand," said Roland, "or we will not be able to escape if <act type="doing"
                        agent="witch" receiver="heroine_roland" effect="hostile">she comes after
                        us."</act></dialogue>
                <act type="doing" agent="heroine" receiver="witch" effect="hostile">The girl got the
                    magic wand,</act> then <act type="doing" agent="heroine"
                    receiver="witch_daughter" effect="ambiguous" io="blood_drops">she took the dead
                    girl's head and dropped three drops of blood onto the floor,</act> one in front
                of the bed, one in the kitchen, and one on the steps. Then <act type="doing"
                    agent="heroine" effect="ambiguous">she hurried away with her
                sweetheart.</act></p>
            <p>The next morning when the old <character reference="witch" child-status="mother"
                    marital-status="unmarried">witch</character> got up, <act type="doing"
                    agent="witch" receiver="witch_daughter" effect="benevolent">she called her
                    daughter, wanting to give her the apron.</act> But <act type="doing"
                    agent="witch_daughter" effect="ambiguous">the daughter did not come.</act> So
                    <dialogue speaker="witch" stateofbeing="neutral">she shouted, "Where are
                    you?"</dialogue>
                <dialogue speaker="first_drop_blood" stateofbeing="neutral">"Here on the steps. I'm
                    sweeping," </dialogue>answered the first drop of blood. The <act type="doing"
                    agent="witch" effect="ambiguous">old woman went out, but seeing no one</act> on
                the steps, <dialogue speaker="witch" stateofbeing="neutral">she shouted again,
                    "Where are you?"</dialogue>
                <dialogue speaker="second_drop_blood" stateofbeing="neutral">"Here in the kitchen.
                    I'm warming myself,"</dialogue> shouted the second drop of blood. <act
                    type="doing" agent="witch" effect="ambiguous">She went into the kitchen, but
                    found no one.</act> So <dialogue speaker="witch" stateofbeing="neutral">she
                    shouted again, "Where are you?"</dialogue>
                <dialogue speaker="third_drop_blood" stateofbeing="neutral">"Here in the bed. I'm
                    sleeping,"</dialogue> shouted the third drop of blood. <act type="doing"
                    agent="witch" effect="ambiguous">She went into the bedroom and approached the
                    bed. What did she see there?</act>
                <act type="being" agent="witch_daughter" receiver="witch" effect="hostile">Her own
                    child swimming in blood</act> and <act type="doing" agent="witch"
                    effect="hostile" receiver="witch_daughter">whose head she herself had cut
                    off.</act></p>
            <p><act type="being" agent="witch" effect="hostile">The <character reference="witch"
                        marital-status="unmarried" child-status="stepmother">witch</character> flew
                    into a rage,</act> jumped to the window, and as <act type="being" agent="witch"
                    effect="hostile">she could see far into the world,</act>
                <act type="doing" agent="witch" receiver="heroine_roland" effect="hostile">she saw
                    her <character child-status="childless" marital-status="unmarried"
                        reference="heroine">stepdaughter</character> hurrying away with her
                    sweetheart Roland.</act>
                <dialogue speaker="witch" stateofbeing="negative">"That won't help you!" shouted the
                        <character child-status="stepmother" marital-status="unmarried"
                        reference="witch">witch</character>.</dialogue>
                <dialogue speaker="witch" stateofbeing="negative">"Even if you've already gone a
                    long way, you won't escape from me!"</dialogue> She put on her many-league
                boots, in which <act type="doing" agent="witch" effect="hostile" io="boots">she
                    covered an hour's walk with every step,</act> and it was not long before <act
                    type="doing" agent="witch" receiver="heroine_roland" effect="hostile">she
                    overtook them.</act> However, <act type="doing" agent="heroine" receiver="witch"
                    effect="ambiguous">when the girl saw the old woman</act> striding toward them,
                    <act type="doing" agent="heroine" receiver="roland" effect="benevolent">she used
                    the magic wand to transform her sweetheart Roland into a lake,</act> and <act
                    type="being" agent="heroine" receiver="self" effect="benevolent">herself into a
                        <character child-status="childless" marital-status="unmarried"
                        reference="heroine">duck</character> swimming in the middle of the
                    lake.</act>
                <act type="doing" agent="witch" receiver="heroine" effect="hostile"><character
                        reference="witch" marital-status="unmarried" child-status="stepmother">The
                        witch</character> stood on the shore and threw in pieces of bread, trying
                    with great effort to lure the duck to her.</act> But <act type="doing"
                    agent="heroine" receiver="witch" effect="hostile"><character reference="heroine"
                        marital-status="unmarried" child-status="childless">the duck</character> did
                    not give in,</act> and <act type="doing" agent="witch" effect="hostile">the
                        <character child-status="stepmother" marital-status="unmarried"
                        reference="witch">old woman</character> had to return home</act> that night
                without success. Afterward <act type="being" agent="heroine"
                    receiver="heroine_roland" effect="benevolent"><character reference="heroine"
                        marital-status="unmarried" child-status="childless">the girl</character> and
                    her sweetheart Roland returned to their natural shapes,</act> and they walked on
                through the whole night until daybreak.<act type="being" agent="heroine"
                    receiver="self" effect="benevolent">Then <character reference="heroine"
                        child-status="childless" marital-status="unmarried">the girl</character>
                    transformed herself into a beautiful <character marital-status="unmarried"
                        child-status="childless" reference="heroine">flower</character></act> in the
                middle of a briar hedge, and<act type="doing" agent="heroine" receiver="roland"
                    effect="benevolent">her sweetheart Roland into a fiddler.</act></p>
            <p>It was not long before <act type="doing" agent="witch" receiver="heroine_roland"
                    effect="hostile">the <character reference="witch" marital-status="unmarried"
                        child-status="stepmother">witch</character> came striding up toward
                    them.</act>
                <dialogue stateofbeing="negative" speaker="witch">She said to the musician, "Dear
                    musician, <act type="doing" agent="witch" receiver="heroine" effect="hostile"
                        >may I pick that beautiful flower for myself?"</act></dialogue>
                <dialogue speaker="roland" stateofbeing="neutral">"Oh, yes," he replied. "And <act
                        type="doing" agent="roland" receiver="witch" effect="hostile">I will play
                        for you</act> while you're doing it."</dialogue>
                <act type="doing" agent="witch" effect="hostile">She crawled hastily into the
                    hedge</act> and <act type="doing" agent="witch" receiver="heroine"
                    effect="hostile">was just about to pick the flower, knowing perfectly well who
                    it was,</act> when <act type="doing" agent="roland" receiver="witch"
                    effect="hostile">he began to play.</act>
                <act type="doing" agent="roland" receiver="witch" effect="hostile">She was forced to
                    dance, whether she wanted to or not, for it was magic dance music.</act>
                <act type="doing" agent="roland" receiver="witch" effect="hostile">The faster he
                    played, the more violently she was forced to jump.</act>
                <act type="doing" agent="roland" receiver="witch" effect="hostile">The thorns tore
                    the clothes off her body, pricking her until she bled,</act> and <act
                    type="doing" agent="roland" receiver="witch" effect="hostile">as he did not
                    stop, she had to dance until she fell down dead.</act></p>
            <p><act type="being" agent="heroine_roland" effect="benevolent">They were now
                    free,</act> so Roland said, <dialogue speaker="roland" stateofbeing="positive"
                    >"Now I will go to my father and <act type="doing" agent="roland"
                        receiver="heroine" effect="benevolent">arrange for our
                    wedding</act>."</dialogue>
                <dialogue speaker="heroine" stateofbeing="positive">"I'll stay here and wait for
                    you," said <character reference="heroine" child-status="childless"
                        marital-status="unmarried">the girl.</character></dialogue>
                <dialogue speaker="heroine" stateofbeing="positive">"And I'll <act type="doing"
                        agent="heroine" receiver="self" effect="benevolent">transform myself into a
                        red boundary stone, so that no one will recognize me."</act></dialogue> So
                Roland set forth, and <act type="doing" agent="heroine" effect="benevolent"
                        ><character marital-status="unmarried" child-status="childless"
                        reference="heroine">the girl,</character> in the shape of a red boundary
                    stone, stood there and waited for her sweetheart.</act> But when Roland arrived
                home, <act type="doing" agent="other_woman" receiver="roland" effect="hostile">he
                    was snared by another woman,</act> who <act type="doing" agent="roland"
                    receiver="heroine" effect="hostile">caused him to forget <character
                        reference="heroine" child-status="childless" marital-status="unmarried">the
                        girl.</character></act>
                <act type="being" agent="heroine" effect="hostile" receiver="self">The poor girl
                    waited there a long time.</act> Finally, when he failed to return, <act
                    type="being" agent="heroine" effect="hostile">she grew sad</act> and <act
                    type="doing" agent="heroine" receiver="self" effect="hostile">transformed
                    herself into a <character marital-status="unmarried" child-status="childless"
                        reference="heroine">flower</character></act>, thinking, <dialogue
                    speaker="heroine" stateofbeing="negative">"Someone will surely come this way and
                    trample me down."</dialogue></p>
            <p>However, it happened that <act type="doing" agent="shepherd" receiver="heroine"
                    effect="ambiguous">a shepherd who was herding his sheep in the field saw the
                        <character reference="heroine" child-status="childless"
                        marital-status="unmarried">flower.</character></act> As it was so beautiful,
                    <act type="doing" agent="shepherd" receiver="heroine" effect="benevolent">he
                    picked it, took it home with him, and put it away in his chest.</act> From that
                time forth, strange things happened in the shepherd's house. <act type="doing"
                    agent="heroine" receiver="shepherd" effect="benevolent">When he arose in the
                    morning all the work was already done.</act>
                <act type="doing" agent="heroine" receiver="shepherd" effect="benevolent">The room
                    was swept,</act>
                <act type="doing" agent="heroine" receiver="shepherd" effect="benevolent">the table
                    and benches cleaned,</act>
                <act type="doing" agent="heroine" receiver="shepherd" effect="benevolent">the fire
                    on the hearth was lighted,</act> and <act type="doing" agent="heroine"
                    receiver="shepherd" effect="benevolent">the water was fetched,</act> and at
                noon, when he came home, <act type="doing" agent="heroine" receiver="shepherd"
                    effect="benevolent">the table was already set,</act> and <act type="doing"
                    agent="heroine" receiver="shepherd" effect="benevolent">a good dinner
                    served.</act> He didn't know how this happened, for <act type="doing"
                    agent="shepherd" effect="ambiguous" io="heroine">he never saw anyone in his
                    house,</act> and no one could have hidden himself in it. <act type="being"
                    agent="shepherd" effect="benevolent" io="heroine">He was, of course, pleased
                    with this good service,</act> but with time he became so afraid that <act
                    type="doing" agent="shepherd" receiver="wise_woman" effect="ambiguous">he went
                    to <character reference="wise_woman" marital-status="unmarried"
                        child-status="childless">a wise woman</character> and asked for her
                    advice.</act> The wise woman said, <dialogue speaker="wise_woman"
                    stateofbeing="positive">"There is magic behind it. Be on the watch very early
                    some morning, and if anything is moving in the room, if you see anything, no
                    matter what it is, throw a white cloth over it, and then the magic will be
                    stopped."</dialogue></p>
            <p><act type="doing" agent="wise_woman" receiver="shepherd" effect="benevolent">The
                    shepherd did what she told him to do,</act> and the next morning just at dawn,
                    <act type="doing" agent="shepherd" receiver="heroine" effect="ambiguous">he saw
                    the chest open and <character child-status="childless"
                        marital-status="unmarried" reference="heroine">the flower</character> come
                    out.</act>
                <act type="doing" agent="shepherd" receiver="heroine" effect="hostile">He quickly
                    jumped towards it and threw a white cloth over it.</act> Instantly <act
                    type="being" agent="heroine" receiver="shepherd" effect="benevolent">the
                    transformation came to an end, and a beautiful <character reference="heroine"
                        marital-status="unmarried" child-status="childless">girl</character> stood
                    before him,</act> who <act type="doing" agent="heroine" receiver="shepherd"
                    effect="benevolent">admitted to him that she had been the flower,</act> and that
                    <act type="doing" agent="heroine" receiver="shepherd" effect="benevolent">she
                    had been doing his housekeeping.</act>
                <act type="doing" agent="heroine" effect="ambiguous">She told him her story.</act>
                <act type="doing" agent="shepherd" receiver="heroine" effect="benevolent">He liked
                    her and asked her to marry him,</act> but <dialogue speaker="heroine"
                    stateofbeing="negative">she answered, "No,"</dialogue> for <act type="doing"
                    agent="heroine" receiver="roland" effect="benevolent">she wanted to remain
                    faithful to her sweetheart Roland,</act> even though <act type="doing"
                    agent="roland" receiver="heroine" effect="hostile">he had abandoned her.</act>
                Nevertheless, <act type="being" agent="heroine" receiver="shepherd"
                    effect="benevolent">she promised not to go away,</act> and to <act type="doing"
                    agent="heroine" receiver="shepherd" effect="benevolent">continue keeping house
                    for the shepherd.</act> The time drew near when <act type="doing" agent="roland"
                    receiver="self" effect="ambiguous">Roland was to be married.</act> According to
                an old custom in that country, it was announced that <act type="doing" agent="girls"
                    receiver="roland" effect="benevolent">all the girls were to attend the
                    wedding</act> and <act type="doing" agent="girls" receiver="roland_other_woman"
                    effect="benevolent">sing in honor of the bridal pair.</act> When the <character
                    child-status="childless" marital-status="unmarried" reference="heroine">faithful
                    girl</character> heard this, <act type="being" agent="heroine" effect="hostile"
                    >she grew so sad that she thought her heart would break,</act> and <act
                    type="doing" agent="heroine" effect="hostile">she did not want to go.</act> But
                    <act type="doing" agent="girls" receiver="heroine" effect="ambiguous">the other
                    girls came and took her.</act>
                <act type="doing" agent="heroine" receiver="roland_other_woman" effect="hostile"
                    >When it was her turn to sing, she declined,</act> until at last <act
                    type="doing" agent="heroine" effect="hostile">she was the only one left, and
                    then she could not refuse.</act> But when <act type="doing" agent="heroine"
                    receiver="roland" effect="benevolent">she began her song, and it reached
                    Roland's ears,</act>
                <dialogue speaker="roland" stateofbeing="positive">he jumped up and shouted, "I know
                    that voice. That is <character reference="heroine" marital-status="unmarried"
                        child-status="childless">the true bride.</character> I do not want anyone
                    else."</dialogue> Everything he had forgotten, and which had vanished from his
                mind, had suddenly come home again to his heart. Thus <act type="doing"
                    agent="roland" receiver="heroine" effect="benevolent">the faithful girl was
                    married to her sweetheart Roland.</act>
                <act type="being" agent="heroine" effect="benevolent">Her grief came to an end, and
                    her joy began.</act></p>
        </story>
    </tale>
    <tale>
        <metadata>
            <title>Der Liebste Roland</title>
            <year>1821</year>
            <author>Jacob Grimm</author>
            <author>Wilhem Grimm</author>
            <language>German</language>
            <number>56</number>
        </metadata>
        <story>
            <p>Es war einmal eine <character child-status="mother" marital-status="unmarried"
                    reference="mother">Mutter</character>, die hatte nur ihre rechte <character
                    child-status="childless" marital-status="unmarried" reference="daughter"
                    >Tochter</character> lieb und <act type="being" effect="hostile" agent="mother"
                    io="stepdaughter">haßte ihre <character child-status="childless"
                        marital-status="unmarried" reference="step-daughter">Stief-
                        tochter</character></act>, <character child-status="childless"
                    marital-status="unmarried" reference="step-daughter">die</character> doch
                tausendmal schöner und besser war. Einmal hatte <character child-status="childless"
                    marital-status="unmarried" reference="step-daughter">diese</character> eine
                schöne Schürze, darüber war die <character child-status="childless"
                    marital-status="unmarried" reference="daughter">andere</character> neidisch und
                verlangte von der <character child-status="mother" marital-status="unmarried"
                    reference="mother">Mutter</character>, <character child-status="mother"
                    marital-status="unmarried" reference="mother">sie</character> solle <character
                    child-status="childless" marital-status="unmarried" reference="daughter"
                    >ihr</character> diese Schürze verschaffen. Die <character child-status="mother"
                    marital-status="unmarried" reference="mother">Mutter</character> sagte:
                    <dialogue speaker="mother" stateofbeing="negative">„sey still, mein liebes
                        <character child-status="childless" marital-status="unmarried"
                        reference="daughter">Kind</character>, du sollst sie haben, deine <character
                        child-status="childless" marital-status="unmarried"
                        reference="step-daughter">Stief- schwester</character> hat doch schon lange
                    den Tod ver- dient, heut Nacht leg dich hinten ins Bett und <act type="doing"
                        effect="hostile" agent="daughter" receiver="step-daughter">schieb <character
                            child-status="childless" marital-status="unmarried"
                            reference="step-daughter">sie</character> recht vorne hin</act>, dann
                    will ich kom- men, wenn sie schläft, und <act type="doing" effect="hostile"
                        agent="mother" receiver="step-daughter">will <character
                            child-status="childless" marital-status="unmarried"
                            reference="step-daughter">ihr</character> den Kopf
                    abhauen.</act>“</dialogue> Die <character child-status="childless"
                    marital-status="unmarried" reference="step-mother">Stiefschwester</character>
                aber hatte in einer Ecke gestanden und alles mit angehört, da ließ <character
                    child-status="childless" marital-status="unmarried" reference="step-daughter"
                    >sie</character> die böse <character child-status="childless"
                    marital-status="unmarried" reference="daughter">Schwester</character> erst zu
                Bett ge- hen, daß sie hinten hin kam, wie sie aber ein- geschlafen war, <act
                    type="doing" effect="hostile" agent="step-daughter" receiver="daughter">hub sie
                    sie auf</act> und legte sie vorne hin, sich aber ganz hinten. Da kam die
                    <character child-status="mother" marital-status="unmarried" reference="mother"
                    >Mutter</character> in der Nacht geschlichen, fühlte erst ob vorne jemand lag
                und schlief, dann faßte <character child-status="mother" marital-status="unmarried"
                    reference="mother">sie</character> die Axt mit beiden Händen und <act
                    type="doing" effect="hostile" agent="mother" receiver="daughter">hieb und hieb
                    ihrem eigenen <character child-status="childless" marital-status="unmarried"
                        reference="daughter">Kind</character> den Kopf ab</act>.</p>

            <p>Wie <character child-status="mother" marital-status="unmarried" reference="mother"
                    >sie</character> fortgegangen war, stand das <character child-status="childless"
                    marital-status="unmarried" reference="step-daughter">Mäd- chen</character> auf
                und ging zu seinem Liebsten Roland, klopfte an und rief: <dialogue
                    speaker="step-daughter" stateofbeing="negative">„hör, wir müssen fort, die
                        <character child-status="mother" marital-status="unmarried"
                        reference="mother">Stiefmutter</character> hat <character
                        child-status="mother" marital-status="unmarried" reference="mother"
                        >ihr</character> eigen <character child-status="childless"
                        marital-status="unmarried" reference="daughter">Kind</character>
                    todtgeschlagen, und meint <character child-status="mother"
                        marital-status="unmarried" reference="mother">sie</character> hätte mich
                    getroffen, kommt der Tag und <character child-status="mother"
                        marital-status="unmarried" reference="mother">sie</character> sieht, was
                        <character child-status="mother" marital-status="unmarried"
                        reference="mother">sie</character> gethan, so bin ich verloren; da hab ich
                    ihren Zauberstab genom- men, damit können wir uns schon helfen.“</dialogue> Der
                Liebste Roland stand auf, und sie nahmen erst den todten Kopf und tröpfelten drei
                Bluts- tropfen, einen vors Bett, einen in die Küche und einen auf die Treppe; darauf
                gingen sie fort. Am Morgen, als die <character child-status="mother"
